article.headline: Dartmouth 76, Vermont 75
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Robbie Pride shook free for a layup and his only two points of the game to give Dartmouth the lead with 7.5 seconds remaining and help the Big Green secure a 76-75 victory over Vermont on Tuesday. Dartmouth forward Alex Barnett led all scorers with a career-high 25 points and 11 rebounds as the Big Green (3-3) broke an eight-game losing streak against defeated Vermont. DeVon Mosley added 17 points for Dartmouth, which rallied from an eight-point deficit with 5:52 left. Marqus Blakely led four Vermont (2-4) scorers in double figures with 23 points and 10 rebounds. Mike Trimboli added 19 points, Kyle Cieplicki 14 and Colin McIntosh 10.
